The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Oct. 12: The Supreme Court has ruled that the income tax department is bound to accept the authenticity of the accounts certified by the auditor and maintained in accordance with the provisions of the Companies Act. The assessing officer will examine whether the books of accounts are duly certified by the authorities under the Companies Act and that such books have been properly maintained.                            
	 New Delhi, Oct. 12: Satyam Computers has no plans to recast t targets despite a financial crisis in the US. We have already given guidance for the year in terms of revenue and recruitments. We will recruit 14,000-15,000 people this year, company chairman Ramalingam Raju said.                            
	 New Delhi, Oct. 12: Fertiliser subsidy, estimated at Rs 1,20,000 crore in the current fiscal, is likely to come down below Rs 1,00,000 crore because of a fall in the prices of major nutrients such as nitrogen and phosphate in the global market.                            
	 New Delhi, Oct. 12: Concerned over the steep fall in the countrys industrial growth, business chamber Ficci has asked the government to cut the rate of corporate tax to the level of competing countries such as China and encourage export of manufacturing goods.                            
	 New Delhi, Oct. 12: Dresdner Bank AG, which was acquired by its rival Commerzbank last month, has decided to surrender the approval received from the Reserve Bank of India to open a banking branch in Mumbai. It will continue to operate from its representative office.                            
	 Calcutta, Oct. 12: Public sector Andrew Yule amp; Company Ltd will invite bids for a stake sale in Dishergarh Power Supply Corporation by the middle of November, a company official said.                            
	 New Delhi, Oct. 12: The department of telecom may find it difficult to segregate revenues between 2G and 3G because of the complex method involved. Trai and CDMA operators feel the separation is tough and can lead to revenue loss.                                                                                                                         
